thread class methods
--------------------

sleep()
-------
method uses to wait a thread for a certain amount of time.
automatically invokes after provided time period
needs to handle exception

yield()
-------
it will stop the currently executiong thread and allows other thread with same priority or higher priority to execute.
automatically invoked by thread scheduler
no need of exception handling

eg:- working
------------

java 5 --> internally it uses sleep method
java 6 --> it it provides a hint to thread scheduler 

join()
------

if a thread wants to wait for another to complete its task we should use join method.
automatically invokes after the completion of another thread task.
need to handle the exception





